human":"Jun 1991","platform":{"id":29,"name":"Sega Mega Drive/Genesis"},"release_region":{"id":1,"region":"europe"}}],"screenshots":[{"id":1347427,"image_id":"scsvoj","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scsvoj.jpg"},{"id":1347428,"image_id":"scsvok","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scsvok.jpg"},{"id":1347429,"image_id":"scsvol","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scsvol.jpg"},{"id":1347430,"image_id":"scsvom","url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/scsvom.jpg"}],"similar_games":[114286,103218,109606,114287,116353,118871,96209,15851,114285,102122],"slug":"final-blow","summary":"Final Blow is a boxing arcade game created in 1988 by Taito. The name would remain the same for all ported platforms, except for the Sega Mega Drive/Genesis versions, which Sega released outside Japan as James 'Buster' Douglas Knockout Boxing featuring Buster Douglas himself in 1990 immediately after his victory over Mike Tyson.\n\nThe game is essentially a side scrolling boxing game where the player moves left and right to control a screen sized boxer. When the timing is right, the player can unleash a final blow punch which can sometimes KO the opponent in a single strike. The home versions contained a spectator mode where the player can watch their favorite boxers compete.","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/final-blow","videos":[{"id":117329,"video_id":"DpcQNR4C3d4"}],"websites":[{"id":19256,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Blow","type":{"id":3,"type":"Wikipedia"}},{"id":358201,"url":"https://www.twitch.tv/directory/game/Final%20Blow","type":{"id":6,"type":"Twitch"}}]}